    "id": 1034070,
    "name": "Ensure strict mode is enabled when creating session (PHP)",
    "href": "AIP/quality-rules/1034070",
    "critical": true,
    "severity": 30,
    "maxWeight": 9,
    "extension": {
        "name": "com.castsoftware.php.security",
        "href": "AIP/extensions/com.castsoftware.php.security"
    },
    "associatedValueName": "Number of violation occurrences",
    "description": "This rule checks all the calls to session_start() without using strict mode.",
    "output": "Associated to each violation, the following information is provided:\n- The number of violation occurrences\n- Bookmarks for violation occurrences found in the source code",
    "rationale": "By crafting a malicious link, an attacker can set a session token of his knowledge into the browser of a victim. When the victim authenticates himself over the web application, the attacker is in the possession of a valid token and can hijack the session of the victim.",
    "reference": "CWE-384: Session Fixation\nhttps://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/384.html\n\nOWASP Top Ten 2021 Category A07:2021 - Identification and Authentication Failures\nhttps://owasp.org/Top10/A07_2021-Identification_and_Authentication_Failures/\n\nPHP: Runtime Configuration - Manual\nhttps://www.php.net/manual/en/session.configuration.php#ini.session.use-strict-mode",
    "remediation": "Set session.use_strict_mode to 'On' in configuration file.\n\nAlternatively, set it with ini_set('session.use_strict_mode', 'On').",
    "remediationSample": "# In source code:\n\nini_set('session.use_strict_mode', 'On');\nsession_start();\n\n# OR in configuration file\n\nsession.use_strict_mode=\"On\"",
    "sample": "# In source code:\n\nsession_start();\n\n# AND in configuration file\n\nsession.use_strict_mode=\"Off\"",
    "total": "Number of PHP artifacts",
    "alternativeName": "Avoid disabling option session.use_strict_mode in configuration file",
